rComments: He made psychometrics as fun as psychometrics could possibly be. It's kind of a boring topic and he understands that. Being a psychometrician himself meant that he knows a lot about the topic and he gives lots of feedback on the data on the midterm and tells you exactly what will be on the midterm and final. I also loved the group project.

AMAZING prof, makes you feel valued and appreciated. He's also hilarious and will crack jokes and share personal experience with the class. No math, just the application of psychometrics. Group project was really long and required effort and he can be picky in grading. His exams are all MCQ but are very tricky, defo read the textbook!!

AMAZING PROF ! If you're enrolled in another Psychometrics class, drop it right now and take it with Christopher instead ! Expectations are super clear, and there is *no stats* He made the material really interesting and fun ! Exams (Two midterms worth 30% each) are very fair if you study for them. The group project worth 40% is easy ! TAKE HIM!

Chris is one of my favourite profs here at UOttawa. His psychometrics class is a blast, and he presents everything in a practical, useful way unlike other profs who just ramble on with theory. Lectures are funny, and he is knowledgeable about many fields and the use of psychometrics. There is a group assignment though, which can be good or bad.

Such a good professor. I don't think i have ever had a course that has been so fair.  Fair grading, fair tests, fair assignments. It is a bit boring but given the subject, psychometrics, you kind of have to expect that.

TAKE HIM. Switch into his class right now. Best prof I have ever had. I usually hate group assignments but he made it easy, understandable, and even fun. He's a super fair marker, his exams are ridiculously fair, and he's a genuinely nice guy. His jokes fall a bit flat, but he made psychometrics (a boring af subject) somewhat interesting!

Professor Chris is great ! he's very down to earth and caring, he cancels questions from the midterm if we don't perform too well on them. Group project worth 40 % but gives very good feedback and helps on them !
